# ðŸ“— Basic Linux Commands

Purpose: Basic navigation, user, and system information commands for everyday use.

---

## ðŸ“˜ Commands:

```bash
pwd                         # Show current directory
ls -la                      # List files with details
cd /var/log                 # Change directory
echo "Hello, Linux!"        # Display text
clear                       # Clear terminal
whoami                      # Show current username
date                        # Display current date/time
cal                         # Show calendar
history                     # Show command history
man ls                      # Open manual page for 'ls'
uname -a                    # Show system info
hostname                    # Display system hostname
uptime                      # How long system is running
who                         # List logged-in users
id                          # Show UID, GID
exit                        # Logout terminal
logout                      # End terminal session
su - username               # Switch to another user
sudo apt update             # Update package lists
passwd                      # Change user password
alias ll="ls -la"           # Create command alias
unalias ll                  # Remove alias
env                         # Show environment variables
export EDITOR=vim           # Set environment variable
printenv PATH               # Show PATH variable
set                         # Show shell variables
read name                   # Prompt for input
sleep 5                     # Pause for 5 seconds
time ls -R /                # Time a command execution
touch file.txt              # Create empty file
cat file.txt                # Show file contents
head -n 10 file.txt         # Show first 10 lines
tail -f /var/log/syslog     # Follow live log
wc -l file.txt              # Count lines
stat file.txt               # Show file details
file script.sh              # Identify file type
basename /home/user/test.txt # Extract filename
dirname /home/user/test.txt # Extract directory path
yes "Running"               # Repeat string until stopped
which python                # Show command path
type ls                     # Show command type
command ls                  # Execute command
eval "echo Hello"           # Evaluate command string
exec bash                   # Replace shell process
printf "Name: %s\n" "Linux" # Formatted output
echo "log" | tee logfile.txt # Output to file and screen
basename /etc/hosts         # Filename only
help cd                     # Help on builtin command
jobs                        # List background jobs
bg %1                       # Resume job in background
